headline: Kenyan Tree,  Century Old,  Gets Reprieve
text: CAIRO — A beloved fig tree in the Kenyan capital, Nairobi, will live to see another day — and, possibly, another century.
snippet: The 100-year-old tree, slated for removal to make room for a new expressway, will be preserved following a backlash from environmentalists concerned about shrinking green spaces in Nairobi.
